Key Match Events: Sean Manaea pitched into the seventh inning of the Mets' 8-3 victory against the Diamondbacks.
Pete Alonso homered to open the scoring.
Manaea retired Arizona in order four times and piled up 11 strikeouts on the night.
Post-Match Reflections: Sean Manaea expressed confidence in his pitches and aggressive approach against hitters.
Manager Carlos Mendoza praised Manaea's hard work and continuous improvement.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played in Phoenix with a temperature of 107 degrees.
The Mets are 18-8 when Manaea starts this season, the highest number of wins behind a starter on the mound.
